SUM.P:
We, the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (Service), change the status of spikedace (
Meda fulgida
) and loach minnow (
Tiaroga cobitis
) from threatened to endangered under the Endangered Species Act of 1973, as amended (Act). With this rule we are also revising the designated critical habitats for both species. These changes fulfill our obligations under a settlement agreement.

